description: Definition of a collection event for a resource
Resource this collection event is part of
Name of the collection event
Description of the collection event
Subpopulations that are targetted by this collection event
Start date of data collection
End date of data collection. Leave empty if collection is ongoing
Age groups included in this data collection event
Number of participants sampled in this data collection event
Areas of information that were extracted in this data collection event
Methods of data collection used in this collection event
Samples that were collected in this collection event
Standardized tools, e.g. surveys, questionnaires, instruments used to collect data for this collection event
If 'other', please specify
Name 10-20 relevant variables that were collected in this collection event
Contact point for this collection event
Organisation that published this collection event
Organisation(s) that created this collection event
When the data for this collection event was first published
When the data for this collection event was last modified
A main category of the collection event. A collection event can have multiple themes. Should at least take default value 'Health' for health data collections

Information that indicates whether the resource is publicly accessible, has access restrictions or is not public. A default is set for non-public access, because most health datasets contain sensitive information and rules and licenses apply to get access

The legislation that mandates the creation or management of the resource. For health datasets, the value must include the ELI of the EHDS Regulation, which is set as a default. URI's to other legislations may be included
